# BMS Hostel — Fix-All Implementation Plan

> Based on the [Implementation Assessment Report](file:///C:/Users/manju/.gemini/antigravity/brain/ca2603d5-5a3e-4e75-8932-90f2dc7c1a61/implementation_assessment.md)

## Correction to Assessment

> [!NOTE]
> During plan research I discovered that the photo upload file filter is applied at the **module level** via `MulterModule.register()` in [uploads.module.ts](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/uploads/uploads.module.ts) (lines 19–24), which validates JPG/PNG/WebP with a 2MB limit. The [uploadPhoto()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/uploads/uploads.controller.ts#42-60) endpoint benefits from this filter even though it doesn't configure one itself. **C1 is mitigated.** The [uploadDocument()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/uploads/uploads.controller.ts#96-114) endpoint overrides the module default with its own inline multer config (5MB, allowing PDF additionally).
>
> Also, [.env](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/.env) is properly gitignored (`.gitignore:13`). **M6 is not an issue** for VCS — but the file does exist on disk and should be kept out of deployment artifacts.

