## Sprint 1 — Critical Security & Quick Fixes

> **Effort: ~1 day** | Focus: security hardening, zero new features

---

### 1.1 Protect uploaded files with auth middleware

Currently files under `/uploads/` are served statically by Express with no auth check. Any URL like `/uploads/photos/<uuid>.jpg` or `/uploads/documents/<uuid>.pdf` is public.

#### [MODIFY] [main.ts](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/main.ts)

- Remove the `app.useStaticAssets(...)` call (lines 17-19)
- File serving will be handled by a new authenticated route instead

#### [NEW] `apps/api/src/uploads/uploads-serve.controller.ts`

- Create a new `GET /uploads/:type/:filename` endpoint
- Guard with `JwtAuthGuard`
- Validate `:type` is `photos` or `documents`
- Use `res.sendFile()` to stream the file from disk
- Return 404 if file doesn't exist

```typescript
@Controller('uploads')
@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)
export class UploadsServeController {
  @Get(':type/:filename')
  serveFile(
    @Param('type') type: string,
    @Param('filename') filename: string,
    @Res() res: Response,
  ) {
    // Validate type, sanitize filename (prevent path traversal),
    // check file exists, send file
  }
}
```

