## Sprint 2 — High-Priority Auth & RBAC Gaps

> **Effort: ~2–3 days** | Focus: password reset, role management API, fix fragile role checks

---

### 2.1 Password Reset Flow

#### [NEW] `apps/api/src/auth/dto/forgot-password.dto.ts`

```typescript
export class ForgotPasswordDto {
  @IsString() identifier: string; // email or mobile
}
```

#### [NEW] `apps/api/src/auth/dto/reset-password.dto.ts`

```typescript
export class ResetPasswordDto {
  @IsString() token: string;
  @IsString() @MinLength(8) newPassword: string;
}
```

#### [MODIFY] [auth.controller.ts](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/auth.controller.ts)

Add two new endpoints:

- `POST /auth/forgot-password` — Public, throttled (3/min). Looks up user by identifier, generates a time-limited reset token (stored hashed in a new `PasswordResetToken` table or repurpose a signed JWT with short expiry + special claim). In Phase 1 (no email), returns the token in the response for dev/testing. In production, this would send an email.
- `POST /auth/reset-password` — Public, throttled. Validates reset token, updates `passwordHash`, revokes all refresh tokens.

#### [MODIFY] [auth.service.ts](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/auth.service.ts)

- Add `forgotPassword(identifier)` and `resetPassword(token, newPassword)` methods

#### [MODIFY] [auth/dto/index.ts](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/dto)

- Export the new DTOs

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since email delivery (Sprint 4) is not yet implemented, the forgot-password endpoint will return the reset token directly in the response body for development, with a clear log warning. When email is wired, this response will be removed and the token sent via email only.

