### 2.3 Fix fragile `user.roles?.includes()` pattern

The JWT payload should be the single source of truth for roles. The issue is in controllers that check `user.roles?.includes('STUDENT')` — if the JWT strategy doesn't populate `roles` as a flat string array, this silently fails.

#### [MODIFY] [auth/strategies/jwt.strategy.ts](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/strategies)

- Verify the `validate()` method returns `{ id, email, roles: string[], permissions: string[] }` consistently
- Add explicit TypeScript type for the return value

#### [MODIFY] Multiple controllers (leave, complaints, violations)

- Replace `user.roles?.includes('STUDENT')` with a helper function:

```typescript
// Add to auth/decorators or a shared utility
export function hasRole(user: any, role: string): boolean {
  return Array.isArray(user.roles) && user.roles.includes(role);
}
```

Files to update:
- `leave.controller.ts:52,78`
- `complaints.controller.ts:53,78`
- `violations.controller.ts:79,97`

---

### 2.4 Migrate token storage from localStorage to httpOnly cookies

#### [MODIFY] [auth.controller.ts](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/auth.controller.ts)

- In [login()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/auth.controller.ts#40-51) and [refresh()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/auth.controller.ts#76-87), set `refreshToken` as an httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict cookie instead of returning in the body
- Access token can remain in the response body (short-lived)
- In [logout()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/auth.controller.ts#95-109), clear the cookie
- Add `@Res({ passthrough: true })` to response handlers

#### [MODIFY] [auth.service.ts](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/auth.service.ts)

- [refresh()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/auth/auth.controller.ts#76-87) reads token from cookie header instead of request body

#### [MODIFY] Web frontend

- Update `apps/web/src/lib/` API client to stop storing refreshToken in localStorage
- Send credentials with `credentials: 'include'` for cookie-based refresh

> [!WARNING]
> This is a **breaking change** for both web and mobile clients. The mobile app will need a separate mechanism (secure storage). Consider making this opt-in via env var `USE_COOKIE_AUTH=true` so both modes can coexist during the transition.

