## Sprint 5 — Mobile App Foundation

> **Effort: ~3–5 days** | Build out essential student-facing screens

This sprint depends on the mobile app requirements. The current shell has only login. Recommended minimum feature set:

#### [MODIFY] `apps/mobile/app/`

Add screens:
- `/dashboard` — Student dashboard (my room, my violations count, pending leave)
- `/leave/new` — Submit leave request
- `/leave/list` — My leave requests
- `/notices` — View notices
- `/complaints/new` — File complaint
- `/profile` — My profile + guardian info
- `/gate` — My gate activity (if student has QR code)

#### [NEW] `apps/mobile/lib/api.ts`

- Axios/fetch wrapper pointing to `APP_URL/api/v1`
- Token storage using `expo-secure-store` (not AsyncStorage/localStorage)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Before starting Sprint 5, we should clarify: **what is the primary mobile user role?** If it's students only, the above is sufficient. If wardens/security also use mobile (e.g., for gate scanning), we need role-based navigation and a camera/QR scanner integration.

