## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

**Existing tests:**
- `apps/api/src/auth/auth.service.spec.ts` — 10 unit tests covering login, logout, profile, signup
- `apps/api/test/auth.e2e-spec.ts` — E2E auth tests

**Commands to run existing tests:**
```bash
# Unit tests
pnpm --filter api test

# E2E tests (requires running DB with seed data)
pnpm --filter api test:e2e
```

**New tests to write:**

| Sprint | Test | Type | File |
|---|---|---|---|
| S1 | Upload serve auth test — verify 401 without token | E2E | `test/uploads.e2e-spec.ts` |
| S1 | Upload serve — verify path traversal is blocked (`../../etc/passwd`) | Unit | `uploads-serve.controller.spec.ts` |
| S2 | Forgot password — verify token generation + reset | Unit | `auth.service.spec.ts` (extend existing) |
| S2 | Role assign — verify assign, duplicate check, revoke | Unit | `users.service.spec.ts` |
| S2 | `hasRole()` helper — verify with missing/empty/valid roles | Unit | `auth/helpers.spec.ts` |
| S3 | Dashboard service — verify no N+1 for login trend | Unit | `dashboard.service.spec.ts` |

### Manual Verification

After each sprint, verify in the browser via Swagger (`http://localhost:3001/api/docs`):

1. **Sprint 1:** Try accessing `/uploads/photos/<any-file>` without Authorization header → should get 401
2. **Sprint 2:** Test forgot-password + reset-password flow via Swagger; test role assign/revoke via `POST/DELETE /users/:id/roles`
3. **Sprint 3:** Call `GET /dashboard/stats` and verify response time is under 500ms (vs current which may spike with data)
4. **Sprint 4:** After wiring email, trigger a leave approval and verify email is sent (check SMTP logs or MailHog)

---

## Execution Order Summary

```
Sprint 1 (Day 1)     → Security hardening, quick fixes
Sprint 2 (Days 2-4)  → Auth gaps (password reset, role API, cookie auth)
Sprint 3 (Day 5)     → Dashboard performance
Sprint 4 (Days 6-10) → Notifications, Mess scaffold, manual violations
Sprint 5 (Days 11-15)→ Mobile app foundation
Sprint 6 (Days 16-17)→ Redis/BullMQ, S3 abstraction
Sprint 7 (Day 18)    → Polish and versioning
```

**Total estimated effort: ~18 working days (3.5 weeks)**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I recommend we execute **Sprint 1 first** since it's pure security fixes with no behavior changes, then proceed to Sprint 2. Each sprint can be reviewed and approved independently.
